rows.field_811025: Prospect was originally looking at a DNS resolution tool that would meet their business needs as they were deploying a new application that would have global users.
Customer wanted to have several applications hosted on premise to use the DNS service.
Client was exploring options where they could deploy their micro services. Client was unsure about traffic and wanted the ability to scale  up and down as needed.
Customer is considering switching to a cloud provider with a larger variety of virtual machines, but is hesitant about the cost of migration vs savings on new virtual machines.
Client is thinking about migrating their primary content store onto a new database service that has more reliability and redundancy.
Prospect was looking to bring in a new set of IoT logs for analysis.
Marketing company was looking to migrate their source databases to our cloud offering to better integrate with other services they are currently using.
Client was looking to deploy a Java application on a container cluster.
Company was looking to deploy a service within a micro service architecture on a managed container cluster.
After switching to our container cluster offering, client wanted to switch DNS resolution service as well.
Client is interested in the streaming data services to track building supplies within all warehouses.

rows.field_818324: "The UI was fantastic when adding any new records or changing any settings."
"It got relatively confusing when making any changes to the records."

"I wish there was more marketing out there about this service, and we never would have started with the previous product we were using in the first place! It took quite a bit of digging to find this service."
"The automatic scalability is exactly what we need. I also love that we can adjust the buffer and batch size at any time without any shard limitations."
"The product did not integrate well with our existing on premise solutions."
"I am very interested in the wide offering of virtual machine configurations."
"The operating systems make it effortless to switch over with a blue/green deployment."
"I wasn't able to find information online quickly about the redundancy, automatic failover, or answers to other questions I had about the database offering."
"There aren't enough virtual server configurations with enough RAM required for our application."
"Although Kubernetes is offered as a service, we would ideally like more features. The functionality is lacking and does not meet our business needs."
"The redundancy and ease of use of the database services makes it the clear winner."
"The price point was higher than what we were comfortable with."
"The functionality seemed to meet our business requirements."
"I would have liked to have more formatting options with the streaming, but I do like the majority of the features."
